tika.dc.description: The gamblers at the Red Fields call Avery Faro a Monster. I call him my cousin. I know about his secret weapon though, the thing that wins him all those fights. Avery can't feel anything, not pain, and not love. We aren't even that close, third cousins, really. But, somewhere along the way, we became closer than that... far too close. Now I think that he's lost it completely. He's jealous. He's possessive. He's hiding something from me. He calls me his Laurel, only his. But I know there are secrets at the Red Fields. By day, Avery is just a regular schoolboy. By night, he morphs into an underground fighter. How can I save Avery from himself?How do you defeat somebody who doesn't even feel?
